newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds stay calm ahead of USDA figures.
newsitem.headline: European feeds stay calm ahead of USDA figures.

text.p: Business on the European meals and feeds market remained very calm this afternoon ahead of Friday's USDA crop and supply/demand figures, dealers said.

Only a few trades were reported this afternoon. Jly/Aug Argentine sunmeal pellets traded at $118 a tonne cif Rotterdam and EU rapemeal changed hands at 23 marks per 100 kg fob lower Rhine and Oct at 23.60 marks, up 0.10 from yesterday.
"The soaring seller prices the last few days and a strong dollar kept most buyers sidelined, waiting for Friday's USDA reports," one broker said.

Dealers said sellers were not eager to sell material this afternoon, anticipating Chicago to rise further after higher than expected U.S. export figures and weather forecasts for more than normal rain and below normal temperatures.
"But liquidation of the July contract sent the whole soy complex well down, supporting the bearish sentiment amongst many operators in Europe," one dealer said.
After around 90 minutes of trading Chicago soymeal futures were $3.6 to $5 lower and soybean futures around 12 cents down.--KAREL LUIMES +31 20 504 5832
